#' @describeIn tm_g_pca sets up the server with reactive graph.

                    		
                  

                  

                    171
                    
                    
                      
#' @inheritParams module_arguments

                    		
                  

                  

                    172
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    173
                    
                    
                      
srv_g_pca <- function(id,

                    		
                  

                  

                    174
                    
                    
                      
                      data,

                    		
                  

                  

                    175
                    
                    
                      
                      filter_panel_api,

                    		
                  

                  

                    176
                    
                    
                      
                      reporter,

                    		
                  

                  

                    177
                    
                    
                      
                      mae_name,

                    		
                  

                  

                    178
                    
                    
                      
                      exclude_assays,

                    		
                  

                  

                    179
                    
                    
                      
                      .test = FALSE) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    180
                    !
                    
                      
  with_reporter <- !missing(reporter) && inherits(reporter, "Reporter")

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    !
                    
                      
  assert_class(filter_panel_api, "FilterPanelAPI")

                    		
                  

                  

                    182
                    !
                    
                      
  checkmate::assert_class(data, "reactive")

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    !
                    
                      
  checkmate::assert_class(shiny::isolate(data()), "teal_data")

                    		
                  

                  

                    184
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    185
                    !
                    
                      
  moduleServer(id, function(input, output, session) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    186
                    !
                    
                      
    teal.logger::log_shiny_input_changes(input, namespace = "teal.modules.hermes")

                    		
                  

                  

                    187
                    !
                    
                      
    output$experiment_ui <- renderUI({

                    		
                  

                  

                    188
                    !
                    
                      
      experimentSpecInput(session$ns("experiment"), data, mae_name)

                    		
                  

                  

                    189
                    
                    
                      
    })

                    		
                  

                  

                    190
                    !
                    
                      
    experiment <- experimentSpecServer(

                    		
                  

                  

                    191
                    !
                    
                      
      "experiment",

                    		
                  

                  

                    192
                    !
                    
                      
      data = data,

                    		
                  

                  

                    193
                    !
                    
                      
      filter_panel_api = filter_panel_api,

                    		
                  

                  

                    194
                    !
                    
                      
      mae_name = mae_name

                    		
                  

                  

                    195
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    196
                    !
                    
                      
    assay <- assaySpecServer(

                    		
                  

                  

                    197
                    !
                    
                      
      "assay",

                    		
                  

                  

                    198
                    !
                    
                      
      assays = experiment$assays,

                    		
                  

                  

                    199
                    !
                    
                      
      exclude_assays = exclude_assays

                    		
                  

                  

                    200
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    201
                    !
                    
                      
    color <- sampleVarSpecServer(

                    		
                  

                  

                    202
                    !
                    
                      
      "color",

                    		
                  

                  

                    203
                    !
                    
                      
      experiment_name = experiment$name,

                    		
                  

                  

                    204
                    !
                    
                      
      original_data = experiment$data

                    		
                  

                  

                    205
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    206
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    207
                    
                    
                      
    # Total number of genes at the moment.

                    		
                  

                  

                    208
                    !
                    
                      
    n_genes <- reactive({

                    		
                  

                  

                    209
                    !
                    
                      
      experiment_data <- color$experiment_data()

                    		
                  

                  

                    210
                    !
                    
                      
      nrow(experiment_data)

                    		
                  

                  

                    211
                    
                    
                      
    })

                    		
                  

                  

                    212
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    213
                    
                    
                      
    # When the total number changes or gene filter is activated, update slider max.

                    		
                  

                  

                    214
                    !
                    
                      
    observeEvent(list(n_genes(), input$filter_top), {

                    		
                  

                  

                    215
                    !
                    
                      
      n_genes <- n_genes()

                    		
                  

                  

                    216
                    !
                    
                      
      filter_top <- input$filter_top

                    		
                  

                  

                    217
                    !
                    
                      
      if (filter_top) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    218
                    !
                    
                      
        n_top <- input$n_top

                    		
                  

                  

                    219
                    !
                    
                      
        updateSliderInput(

                    		
                  

                  

                    220
                    !
                    
                      
          session = session,

                    		
                  

                  

                    221
                    !
                    
                      
          inputId = "n_top",

                    		
                  

                  

                    222
                    !
                    
                      
          value = min(n_top, n_genes),

                    		
                  

                  

                    223
                    !
                    
                      
          max = n_genes

                    		
                  

                  

                    224
                    
                    
                      
        )

                    		
                  

                  

                    225
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    226
                    
                    
                      
    })

                    		
                  

                  

                    227
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    228
                    
                    
                      
    # When the chosen experiment or assay name changes, recompute the PC.

                    		
                  

                  

                    229
                    !
                    
                      
    pca_result <- reactive({

                    		
                  

                  

                    230
                    !
                    
                      
      experiment_data <- color$experiment_data()

                    		
                  

                  

                    231
                    !
                    
                      
      filter_top <- input$filter_top

                    		
                  

                  

                    232
                    !
                    
                      
      n_top <- input$n_top

                    		
                  

                  

                    233
                    !
                    
                      
      assay_name <- assay()

                    		
                  

                  

                    234
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    235
                    !
                    
                      
      validate(need(hermes::is_hermes_data(experiment_data), "please use HermesData() on input experiments"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    236
                    !
                    
                      
      req(isTRUE(assay_name %in% SummarizedExperiment::assayNames(experiment_data)))

                    		
                  

                  

                    237
                    !
                    
                      
      validate(need(

                    		
                  

                  

                    238
                    !
                    
                      
        ncol(experiment_data) > 2,

                    		
                  

                  

                    239
                    !
                    
                      
        "Sample size is too small. PCA needs more than 2 samples."

                    		
                  

                  

                    240
                    
                    
                      
      ))

                    		
                  

                  

                    241
                    !
                    
                      
      validate(need(

                    		
                  

                  

                    242
                    !
                    
                      
        nrow(experiment_data) > 1,

                    		
                  

                  

                    243
                    !
                    
                      
        "Number of genes is too small. PCA needs more than 1 gene."

                    		
                  

                  

                    244
                    
                    
                      
      ))

                    		
                  

                  

                    245
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    246
                    !
                    
                      
      hermes::calc_pca(experiment_data, assay_name, n_top = if (filter_top) n_top else NULL)

                    		
                  

                  

                    247
                    
                    
                      
    })

                    		
                  

                  

                    248
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    249
                    
                    
                      
    # When experiment or assay name changes, update choices for PCs in x_var and y_var.

                    		
                  

                  

                    250
                    !
                    
                      
    observeEvent(pca_result(), {

                    		
                  

                  

                    251
                    !
                    
                      
      pca_result_x <- pca_result()$x

                    		
                  

                  

                    252
                    !
                    
                      
      pc_choices <- seq_len(ncol(pca_result_x))

                    		
                  

                  

                    253
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    254
                    !
                    
                      
      id_names <- c("x_var", "y_var")

                    		
                  

                  

                    255
                    !
                    
                      
      for (i in seq_along(id_names)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    256
                    !
                    
                      
        updateSelectizeInput(

                    		
                  

                  

                    257
                    !
                    
                      
          session,

                    		
                  

                  

                    258
                    !
                    
                      
          id_names[i],

                    		
                  

                  

                    259
                    !
                    
                      
          choices = pc_choices,

                    		
                  

                  

                    260
                    !
                    
                      
          selected = pc_choices[i]

                    		
                  

                  

                    261
                    
                    
                      
        )

                    		
                  

                  

                    262
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    263
                    
                    
                      
    })

                    		
                  

                  

                    264
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    265
                    
                    
                      
    # Compute correlation of PC with sample variables.

                    		
                  

                  

                    266
                    !
                    
                      
    cor_result <- reactive({

                    		
                  

                  

                    267
                    !
                    
                      
      pca_result <- pca_result()

                    		
                  

                  

                    268
                    !
                    
                      
      experiment_data <- color$experiment_data()

                    		
                  

                  

                    269
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    270
                    !
                    
                      
      hermes::correlate(pca_result, experiment_data)

                    		
                  

                  

                    271
                    
                    
                      
    })

                    		
                  

                  

                    272
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    273
                    
                    
                      
    # Compute & display PCA matrix table if show_matrix is TRUE.

                    		
                  

                  

                    274
                    !
                    
                      
    show_matrix_pca <- reactive({

                    		
                  

                  

                    275
                    !
                    
                      
      if (input$show_matrix) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    276
                    !
                    
                      
        pca_result_x <- pca_result()$x

                    		
                  

                  

                    277
                    !
                    
                      
        pca_result_x <- round(pca_result_x, 3)

                    		
                  

                  

                    278
                    !
                    
                      
        as.data.frame(pca_result_x)

                    		
                  

                  

                    279
                    
                    
                      
      } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    280
                    !
                    
                      
        NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    281
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    282
                    
                    
                      
    })

                    		
                  

                  

                    283
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    284
                    !
                    
                      
    output$table_pca <- DT::renderDT({

                    		
                  

                  

                    285
                    !
                    
                      
      show_matrix_pca <- show_matrix_pca()

                    		
                  

                  

                    286
                    !
                    
                      
      DT::datatable(

                    		
                  

                  

                    287
                    !
                    
                      
        show_matrix_pca,

                    		
                  

                  

                    288
                    !
                    
                      
        rownames = TRUE,

                    		
                  

                  

                    289
                    !
                    
                      
        options = list(scrollX = TRUE, pageLength = 30, lengthMenu = c(5, 15, 30, 100)),

                    		
                  

                  

                    290
                    !
                    
                      
        caption = "PCA Matrix"

                    		
                  

                  

                    291
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    292
                    
                    
                      
    })

                    		
                  

                  

                    293
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    294
                    
                    
                      
    # Compute & display correlation matrix if show_matrix is TRUE

                    		
                  

                  

                    295
                    !
                    
                      
    show_matrix_cor <- reactive({

                    		
                  

                  

                    296
                    !
                    
                      
      if (input$show_matrix) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    297
                    !
                    
                      
        cor_result <- cor_result()

                    		
                  

                  

                    298
                    !
                    
                      
        cor_result <- round(cor_result, 3)

                    		
                  

                  

                    299
                    !
                    
                      
        as.data.frame(cor_result)

                    		
                  

                  

                    300
                    
                    
                      
      } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    301
                    !
                    
                      
        NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    302
                    
                    
                      
      }

                    		
                  

                  

                    303
                    
                    
                      
    })

                    		
                  

                  

                    304
                    !
                    
                      
    output$table_cor <- DT::renderDT({

                    		
                  

                  

                    305
                    !
                    
                      
      show_matrix_cor <- show_matrix_cor()

                    		
                  

                  

                    306
                    !
                    
                      
      DT::datatable(

                    		
                  

                  

                    307
                    !
                    
                      
        show_matrix_cor,

                    		
                  

                  

                    308
                    !
                    
                      
        rownames = TRUE,

                    		
                  

                  

                    309
                    !
                    
                      
        options = list(scrollX = TRUE, pageLength = 30, lengthMenu = c(5, 15, 30, 100)),

                    		
                  

                  

                    310
                    !
                    
                      
        caption = "PC and Sample Correlation Matrix"

                    		
                  

                  

                    311
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    312
                    
                    
                      
    })

                    		
                  

                  

                    313
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    314
                    
                    
                      
    # Render plot PCA output.

                    		
                  

                  

                    315
                    !
                    
                      
    plot_pca <- reactive({

                    		
                  

                  

                    316
                    
                    
                      
      # Resolve all reactivity.

                    		
                  

                  

                    317
                    !
                    
                      
      pca_result <- pca_result()

                    		
                  

                  

                    318
                    !
                    
                      
      experiment_data <- color$experiment_data()

                    		
                  

                  

                    319
                    !
                    
                      
      x_var <- as.numeric(input$x_var)

                    		
                  

                  

                    320
                    !
                    
                      
      y_var <- as.numeric(input$y_var)

                    		
                  

                  

                    321
                    !
                    
                      
      data <- as.data.frame(SummarizedExperiment::colData(color$experiment_data()))

                    		
                  

                  

                    322
                    !
                    
                      
      color_var <- color$sample_var()

                    		
                  

                  

                    323
                    !
                    
                      
      assay_name <- assay()

                    		
                  

                  

                    324
                    !
                    
                      
      var_pct <- input$var_pct

                    		
                  

                  

                    325
                    !
                    
                      
      label <- input$label

                    		
                  

                  

                    326
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    327
                    
                    
                      
      # Require which states need to be truthy.

                    		
                  

                  

                    328
                    !
                    
                      
      req(

                    		
                  

                  

                    329
                    !
                    
                      
        assay_name,

                    		
                  

                  

                    330
                    
                    
                      
        # Note: The following statements are important to make sure the UI inputs have been updated.

                    		
                  

                  

                    331
                    !
                    
                      
        isTRUE(assay_name %in% SummarizedExperiment::assayNames(experiment_data)),

                    		
                  

                  

                    332
                    !
                    
                      
        is.null(color_var) || isTRUE(color_var %in% names(SummarizedExperiment::colData(experiment_data))),

#' Helper Function to Update Gene Selection

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    
                    
                      
#' @description `r lifecycle::badge("experimental")`

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    
                    
                      
#' This helper function takes the intersection of `selected` and

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    
                    
                      
#' `choices` for genes and updates the `inputId` accordingly. It then

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    
                    
                      
#' shows a notification if not all `selected` genes were available.

                    		
                  

                  

                    142
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    
                    
                      
#' @inheritParams module_arguments

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    
                    
                      
#' @param session (`ShinySession`)\cr the session object.

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    
                    
                      
#' @param selected (`character`)\cr currently selected gene IDs.

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    
                    
                      
#' @param choices (`data.frame`)\cr containing `id` and `name` columns of the

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    
                    
                      
#'   new choices.

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    
                    
                      
h_update_gene_selection <- function(session,

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    
                    
                      
                                    inputId, # nolint

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    
                    
                      
                                    selected,

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    
                    
                      
                                    choices) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    !
                    
                      
  is_new_selected <- selected %in% choices$id

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    !
                    
                      
  is_removed <- !is_new_selected

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    !
                    
                      
  updateSelectizeInput(

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    !
                    
                      
    session = session,

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    !
                    
                      
    inputId = inputId,

                    		
                  

                  

                    159
                    !
                    
                      
    selected = selected[is_new_selected],

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    !
                    
                      
    choices = stats::setNames(choices$id, choices$name),

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    !
                    
                      
    server = TRUE

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    164
                    !
                    
                      
  n_removed <- sum(is_removed)

                    		
                  

                  

                    165
                    !
                    
                      
  if (n_removed > 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    !
                    
                      
    showNotification(paste(

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    !
                    
                      
      "Removed", n_removed, ifelse(n_removed > 1, "genes", "gene"),

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    !
                    
                      
      hermes::h_parens(hermes::h_short_list(selected[is_removed]))

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    
                    
                      
    ))

                    		
                  

                  

                    170
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    171
                    
                    
                      
}

#' Helper Function to Parse Genes

                    		
                  

                  

                    174
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    175
                    
                    
                      
#' @description `r lifecycle::badge("experimental")`

                    		
                  

                  

                    176
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    177
                    
                    
                      
#' This helper function takes a vector of `words` and tries to match them

                    		
                  

                  

                    178
                    
                    
                      
#' with the `id` and `name` columns of possible gene choices.

                    		
                  

                  

                    179
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    180
                    
                    
                      
#' @param words (`character`)\cr containing gene IDs or names.

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    
                    
                      
#' @inheritParams h_update_gene_selection

                    		
                  

                  

                    182
                    
                    
                      
#' @return The subset of `choices` which matches `words` in ID or name.

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    184
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    185
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    186
                    
                    
                      
#' h_parse_genes(

                    		
                  

                  

                    187
                    
                    
                      
#'   c("a", "2535"),

                    		
                  

                  

                    188
                    
                    
                      
#'   data.frame(id = as.character(2533:2537), name = letters[1:5])

                    		
                  

                  

                    189
                    
                    
                      
#' )

                    		
                  

                  

                    190
                    
                    
                      
h_parse_genes <- function(words, choices) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    191
                    2x
                    
                      
  assert_character(words, min.len = 1L)

                    		
                  

                  

                    192
                    2x
                    
                      
  assert_data_frame(choices, types = "character")

                    		
                  

                  

                    193
                    2x
                    
                      
  assert_set_equal(names(choices), c("id", "name"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    194
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    195
                    2x
                    
                      
  id_matches <- choices$id %in% words

                    		
                  

                  

                    196
                    2x
                    
                      
  name_matches <- choices$name %in% words

                    		
                  

                  

                    197
                    2x
                    
                      
  has_match <- id_matches | name_matches

                    		
                  

                  

                    198
                    2x
                    
                      
  choices[has_match, , drop = FALSE]

                    		
                  

                  

                    199
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                  

                    200

      gene_text <- input$gene_text

                    !
                    
                      
      gene_choices <- gene_choices()

                    		
                  

                  

                    409
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    410
                    !
                    
                      
      if (!nzchar(gene_text)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    411
                    !
                    
                      
        showNotification(

                    		
                  

                  

                    412
                    !
                    
                      
          "Please enter at least one full gene ID.",

          type = "error"

        )

                    		
                  

                  

                    415

                    416

                    417
                    !
                    
                      
        parse_result <- h_parse_genes(words, choices = gene_choices)

                    		
                  

                  

                    418
                    !

        parsed_genes(parse_result)

    # When the gene choice is updated, then also set the names

                    		
                  

                  

                    427
                    
                    
                      
    # correctly by looking up in current choices.

                    		
                  

                  

                    428
                    !
                    
                      
    named_genes <- eventReactive(input$genes, ignoreNULL = FALSE, {

                    		
                  

                  

                    429
                    !
                    
                      
      genes <- input$genes

                    		
                  

                  

                    430
                    !
                    
                      
      gene_choices <- gene_choices()

                    !

        which_id <- match(genes, gene_choices$id)

                    		
                  

                  

                    433
                    !
                    
                      
        gene_names <- gene_choices$name[which_id]

                    		
                  

                  

                    434
                    !
                    
                      
        stats::setNames(genes, gene_names)

                    		
                  

                  

                    435

                    436

        NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    437

      ret

                    !
                    
                      
    reactive({

                    		
                  

                  

                    442

      hermes::gene_spec(

                    		
                  

                  

                    443

        genes = named_genes(),

                    		
                  

                  

                    444

        fun = funs[[input$fun_name]],

                    		
                  

                  

                    445
                    !
                    
                      
        fun_name = input$fun_name

                    		
                  

                  

                    446
                    
                    
                      
      )

  })

#' Validation of Gene Specification

                    		
                  

                  

                    452
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    453
                    
                    
                      
#' @description `r lifecycle::badge("experimental")`

                    		
                  

                  

                    454
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    455
                    
                    
                      
#' This validation function checks that a given [`hermes::GeneSpec`] has at least

                    		
                  

                  

                    456
                    
                    
                      
#' one gene selected and that all genes are included in possible choices.

                    		
                  

                  

                    457
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    458
                    
                    
                      
#' @param gene_spec (`GeneSpec`)\cr gene specification.

                    		
                  

                  

                    459
                    
                    
                      
#' @param gene_choices (`character`)\cr all possible gene choices.

                    		
                  

                  

                    460
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    461
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    462
                    
                    
                      
validate_gene_spec <- function(gene_spec,

                    		
                  

                  

                    463
                    
                    
                      
                               gene_choices) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    464
                    !
                    
                      
  assert_r6(gene_spec, "GeneSpec")

                    		
                  

                  

                    465
                    !
                    
                      
  assert_character(gene_choices)

                    		
                  

                  

                    466
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    467
                    !
                    
                      
  validate(need(

                    		
                  

                  

                    468
                    !
                    
                      
    !is.null(gene_spec$get_genes()),

                    		
                  

                  

                    469
                    !
                    
                      
    "please select at least one gene"

                    		
                  

                  

                    470
                    
                    
                      
  ))

                    		
                  

                  

                    471
                    !
                    
                      
  genes_not_included <- setdiff(gene_spec$get_genes(), gene_choices)

                    		
                  

                  

                    472
                    !
                    
                      
  n_not_incl <- length(genes_not_included)

                    		
                  

                  

                    473
                    !
                    
                      
  validate(need(

                    		
                  

                  

                    474
                    !
                    
                      
    identical(n_not_incl, 0L),

                    		
                  

                  

                    475
                    !
                    
                      
    paste(

                    		
                  

                  

                    476
                    !
                    
                      
      n_not_incl,

                    		
                  

                  

                    477
                    !
                    
                      
      ifelse(n_not_incl > 1, "genes", "gene"),

                    		
                  

                  

                    478
                    !
                    
                      
      hermes::h_parens(hermes::h_short_list(genes_not_included)),

                    		
                  

                  

                    479
                    !
                    
                      
      "not included, please unlock or change filters"

                    		
                  

                  

                    480
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    481
                    
                    
                      
  ))

                    		
                  

                  

                    482
                    
                    
                      
}

#' Data Preprocessing for `ADTTE` Module

                    9x
                    
                      
    x = hd_usubjid,

                    9x
                    
                      
    choices = sm_usubjid

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    8x
                    
                      
  mae_coldata <- MultiAssayExperiment::colData(mae)

  if (usubjid_var %in% colnames(mae_coldata)) {

                    71
                    8x
                    
                      
      x = sm_usubjid,

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    8x
                    
                      
      choices = mae_usubjid

  gene_data <- hermes::col_data_with_genes(

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    7x
                    
                      
    object = hd,

                    7x
                    
                      
    assay_name = assay_name,

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    7x
                    
                      
    genes = genes

  )

#' Module Input for `ADTTE` Specification

                    3x

#' Module Server for `ADTTE` Specification

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    
                    
                      
#' @description `r lifecycle::badge("experimental")`

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    
                    
                      
#' This defines the server part for the `ADTTE` specification. The resulting data

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    
                    
                      
#' set `binned_adtte_subset` contains the subset of `ADTTE` selected by the time-to-event

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    
                    
                      
#' endpoint, joined together with the gene information extracted from specified assay

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    
                    
                      
#' and experiment, as numeric and factor columns. The factor column is created by binning

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    
                    
                      
#' the numeric column according to the quantile cutoffs specified in `probs`.

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    
                    
                      
#' @inheritParams module_arguments

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    
                    
                      
#' @param experiment_data (reactive `AnyHermesData`)\cr input experiment.

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    
                    
                      
#' @param experiment_name (reactive `string`)\cr name of the input experiment.

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    
                    
                      
#' @param assay (reactive `string`)\cr name of the assay.

                    		
                  

                  

                    135
                    
                    
                      
#' @param genes (reactive `GeneSpec`)\cr gene specification.

                    		
                  

                  

                    136
                    
                    
                      
#' @param probs (reactive `numeric`)\cr probabilities to bin the gene or gene signature

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    
                    
                      
#'   into.

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    
                    
                      
#' @return List with the following elements:

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    
                    
                      
#'   - `binned_adtte_subset`: reactive containing the joined `ADTTE` and gene data.

                    		
                  

                  

                    141

                    142
                    
                    
                      
#'        numeric gene variable.

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    
                    
                      
#'   - `gene_factor`: string with the variable name for the binned gene data.

                    		
                  

                  

                    144

                    145

                    146

                    147
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    
                    
                      
#' @export

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    150

                    151

adtteSpecServer <- function(id, # nolint

                    		
                  

                  

                    244
                    
                    
                      
                            data,

                    		
                  

                  

                    245
                    
                    
                      
                            mae_name,

                    		
                  

                  

                    246

  assert_string(id)

  assert_string(mae_name)

  moduleServer(id, function(input, output, session) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    266
                    !
                    
                      
    teal.logger::log_shiny_input_changes(input, namespace = "teal.modules.hermes")

                    		
                  

                  

                    267
                    
                    
                      
    # Join ADTTE with gene data.

                    		
                  

                  

                    268
                    !
                    
                      
    adtte_joined <- reactive({

                    		
                  

                  

                    269
                    !
                    
                      
      experiment_data <- experiment_data()

                    		
                  

                  

                    270
                    !
                    
                      
      experiment_name <- experiment_name()

                    		
                  

                  

                    271
                    !
                    
                      
      assay <- assay()

                    		
                  

                  

                    272
                    !
                    
                      
      genes <- genes()

                    		
                  

                  

                    273
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    274
                    !
                    
                      
      validate_gene_spec(genes, rownames(experiment_data))

                    		
                  

                  

                    275
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    276
                    !

                    277
                    !
                    
                      
        genes$returns_vector(),

                    		
                  

                  

                    278
                    !
                    
                      
        experiment_name,

                    		
                  

                  

                    279
                    !
                    
                      
        assay

                    		
                  

                  

                    280

                    281
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    282
                    !
                    
                      
      mae <- data()[[mae_name]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    283
                    !
                    
                      
      adtte <- data()[[adtte_name]]

                    		
                  

                  

                    284
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    285
                    !
                    
                      
      mae[[experiment_name]] <- experiment_data

                    		
                  

                  

                    286
                    !
                    
                      
      h_km_mae_to_adtte(

                    		
                  

                  

                    287
                    !
                    
                      
        adtte,

                    		
                  

                  

                    288

        mae,

                    		
                  

                  

                    289
                    !
                    
                      
        genes = genes,

                    		
                  

                  

                    290
                    !
                    
                      
        experiment_name = experiment_name,

                    		
                  

                  

                    291
                    !
                    
                      
        assay_name = assay,

                    		
                  

                  

                    292
                    !
                    
                      
        usubjid_var = adtte_vars$usubjid

                    		
                  

                  

                    293
                    
                    
                      
      )

                    		
                  

                  

                    294
                    
                    
                      
    })

                    !

      attr(adtte_joined(), "gene_cols")

                    		
                  

                  

                    298

                    300
                    
                    
                      
    # After joining, we recompute available endpoints.

                    		
                  

                  

                    301
                    !
                    
                      
    paramcd_choices <- reactive({

                    		
                  

                  

                    302
                    !
                    
                      
      adtte_joined <- adtte_joined()

                    		
                  

                  

                    303
                    !
                    
                      
      sort(unique(adtte_joined[[adtte_vars$paramcd]])) # Order should not matter.

                    		
                  

                  

                    304
                    
                    
                      
    })

                    		
                  

                  

                    305
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    306
                    
                    
                      
    # Once available endpoints change, we update choices (and also the selection

                    		
                  

                  

                    307
                    
                    
                      
    # if nothing was selected earlier) and warn the user if previous endpoint is

                    		
                  

                  

                    308
                    
                    
                      
    # not available.

                    		
                  

                  

                    309
                    !
                    
                      
    observeEvent(paramcd_choices(), {

                    		
                  

                  

                    310
                    !
                    
                      
      paramcd_choices <- paramcd_choices()

                    		
                  

                  

                    311
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    312
                    !
                    
                      
      new_selected <- if (is_blank(input$paramcd) || (input$paramcd %in% paramcd_choices)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    313
                    !
                    
                      
        input$paramcd

                    		
                  

                  

                    314
                    
                    
                      
      } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    315
                    !
                    
                      
        showNotification(type = "warning", paste(

                    		
                  

                  

                    316
                    !

                    318

                    319

                    320

                    321
                    !
                    
                      
      updateSelectizeInput(

                    !

                    325
                    !
                    
                      
        session = session

                    		
                  

                  

                    326

                    327
                    
                    
                      
    })

                    		
                  

                  

                    328
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    329
                    
                    
                      
    # Subset zooming in on a specified endpoint.

                    		
                  

                  

                    330
                    !
                    
                      
    adtte_subset <- reactive({

                    		
                  

                  

                    331
                    !
                    
                      
      endpoint <- input$paramcd

                    		
                  

                  

                    332
                    !
                    
                      
      adtte_joined <- adtte_joined()

                    		
                  

                  

                    333
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    334
                    !
                    
                      
      validate(need(

                    		
                  

                  

                    335
                    !
                    
                      
        endpoint,

                    		
                  

                  

                    336
                    !
                    
                      
        "please select an endpoint"

                    		
                  

                  

                    337

                    338

                    339
                    !

                    340
                    !
                    
                      
        nrow(adtte_joined) > 0,

                    		
                  

                  

                    341
                    !

                    342

                    343
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    344
